commit.message:
Approximate GHC's old atomic barriers with C11 fences

As of GHC 9.9 the old-style Cmm atomic barriers have been removed. We
now approxiate them with C11 atomic fences.

Addresses #88.

Co-authored-by: Ryan Scott <ryan.gl.scott@gmail.com>

chaselev-deque: Document 0.5.0.5 in CHANGELOG

As noticed in #85, the `CHANGELOG` was missing for this version in particular.

lockfree-queue: Fix the build with GHC 9.4

`sameMutVar#` is no longer provided by `GHC.PrimopWrappers`, but rather
`GHC.Exts`. This patch changes the imports to use `GHC.Exts`, which both
fixes the issue and should be more future-proof.

Fixes #83.

Remove >= from Cabal-version (#81)

Hopefully this suppresses the following warning:

```
Warning: atomic-primops.cabal:10:28: Packages with 'cabal-version: 1.12' or
later should specify a specific version of the Cabal spec of the form
```

commit.message:
Import unsafeCoerce# from GHC.Exts, not GHC.Prim

`atomic-primops` and `chaselev-deque` fail to build on GHC HEAD
(8.11) since `unsafeCoerce#` can no longer be imported from
`GHC.Prim` (see
https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/commit/74ad75e87317196c600dfabc61aee1b87d95c214).
Luckily, `GHC.Exts` provides a backwards-compatible way to import
`unsafeCoerce#`, so we can simply import it from there instead.

Delete unnecessary CPP

All of the libraries in `haskell-lockfree` support GHC 7.10 as the
minimum, which makes a large amount of the CPP unnecessary. Let's
delete it.
